rComments: Hes great at getting you inspired but getting midterms back everyone was shocked at how poorly we all did. His attitude changed for us when we got the first midterm back. rComments: Good prof overall, had a mini quiz every lecture but they were free marks if you were on top of the material. Gave really good advice for undergrads at the beginning of the each lecture too. Conveys ideas easily and will go over them if you do not understand. Overall a great prof, really cares about how students learn. In my top 5 for sure.
Not accessible outside of class, and does not provide adequate feedback.

He's very nice and considerate. The course is not extremely hard, but it certainly isn't as easy as he thinks it is. It requires A LOT of memorization for the test and final exam. In-class quizzes boost your mark a lot /if you do the readings before class/. So do them. More than any other class, keep up with your studying over the semester.
